Old vaccines protected against three strains, which included two varieties of type A viruses and only one variety of the type B virus. Now, some of the vaccines will include one more variety of the type B virus. Since the quadrivalent strain is new, vaccines that require needle injections will be limited. However, all nasal sprays will have all four varieties. Nasal sprays will be made with a live but weakened version of the virus and thus, only healthy people between the ages of two and 49 would qualify for this type of vaccine.
